items.name: Golden Tofu Scramble

ingredients.name: 1 cup shredded kale, or baby spinach
1 dash hot sauce, to taste, optional
16 ounce firm tofu, or extra-firm, pressed and drained

items.directions:
Add oil to a large skillet set over medium heat. Once hot, add garlic and onion, cooking for about 3-4 minutes or until onions begin to soften.

Add mushrooms to the pan, then use your fingers to crumble the tofu into chunks before tossing it into the pan as well. Cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. If the tofu starts to stick or the pan becomes dry, add a little water to the pan.

Add the turmeric, cumin, salt and pepper and stir to combine. Then add the kale and nutritional yeast. Stir and cook for an additional 3-4 minutes. Taste and season with additional black pepper and sea salt, if needed. Serve the scramble warm with sliced avocado and fresh herbs.

items.name: Vietnamese-Style Shaking Beef and Watercress

ingredients.name: 1/2 bunch  watercress (3 oz), cut into 2-inch lengths
1 1/4 pound grass-fed NY strip beef or tenderloin, fat trimmed, cut into 1-inch cubes

semantics.food: grass-fed NY strip beef or tenderloin

ingredients.name: 1/2 cup red onions, very thinly sliced

items.directions:
In a large bowl, whisk together the lime juice, 2 teaspoons of the safflower oil, fish sauce, honey and Sriracha until the honey has dissolved. Set aside. Arrange the watercress and tomato slices on a serving platter, set aside.

Toss the beef with the five-spice powder, salt and pepper. Heat a wok or large cast-iron skillet over high heat and add the remaining tablespoon of oil. When the oil is very hot, add the beef and onions and cook without stirring until the beef is browned on one side, about 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in the garlic and continue to cook until the beef is browned all over but still pink in the center, about 1 1/2–2 minutes more.

Transfer the beef and onion mixture to the serving platter. Drizzle the lime juice mixture over the top and serve immediately.

items.name: Overnight Oats

ingredients.name: 1/4 cup (60 ml) 2% milk or unsweetened non-dairy
2 teaspoons canola oil or melted coconut oil

semantics.food: canola oil or melted coconut oil

items.directions: In a small bowl, whisk together the flour, oats, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. In a small measuring cup, whisk together the milk, oil and vanilla. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix with a fork until moistened. Stir in the blueberries.\n\nSpoon the batter into a 12–16-ounce (450–473ml) mug. Sprinkle the top with nuts. Microwave on high until the cake has expanded and is firm to the touch, 1 1/2–2 minutes, depending on the wattage of your microwave. Watch closely and do not overcook. Add time in 10-second intervals if the muffin is not done. The muffin will puff up at first, but deflate as it cools.

items.name: Protein-Packed Overnight Oats

ingredients.name: 1/2 cup old fashioned oats, certified gluten-free if necessary

items.directions: Combine oats, milk, yogurt, almond butter, honey, spice, and apple in a 1-cup jar, stirring until very well blended. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.\n\nStir before serving and sprinkle with walnuts.

items.name: Pumpkin Pie Oatmeal

ingredients.name: 2 1/2 cup uncooked quick oats, certified gluten-free, if necessary
1/4 cup canned pumpkin puree, certified gluten-free if necessary

items.directions:
In a saucepan, combine milk and water and heat over medium-low heat for 2–3 minutes. Add oats, pumpkin puree, vanilla extract, salt and pumpkin pie spice to the pot, then stir until well combined. Allow the oatmeal to simmer for 2–3 minutes.

If the oatmeal is too thick, stir in a tablespoon of water at a time until it reaches the desired consistency.

Add honey, and stir. Enjoy!

items.name: Shredded Vegetable Salad With Sesame Chicken Strips
items.directions:
Preheat the oven to 400ºF (205ºC). Line a small sheet pan with parchment paper and reserve.

In a large bowl, combine the cabbage, carrots and radishes. In a cup, combine the tahini, tamari, rice vinegar, honey and ginger and stir well. Pour over the vegetables and toss to coat.

Cut the chicken into 6 even slices, across the grain. Place the egg white in a medium bowl and whisk with 1 teaspoon water. Place the sesame seeds in a medium bowl. Dip the chicken in the egg white, then seeds, then place on the parchment-lined pan.

Bake for 10 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through.

items.name: Cacao Nib & Almond Green Smoothie Bowl

ingredients.name: 2 tablespoon whole raw almonds, coarsely chopped

items.directions:
Place 2 teaspoons of the cacao nibs in the container of a powerful blender. Add the yogurt, almond butter, frozen banana, spinach and oats and blend, tamping or scraping down to make a smooth puree.

Divide between two cereal bowls and smooth the mixture. Arrange the banana slices, raspberries, chopped almonds and remaining cacao nibs on top of the smoothie.

Serve immediately with a spoon.

items.name: High-Protein Chicken Salad

ingredients.name: 1 pound cooked chicken breast or rotisserie chicken, shredded (about 4 cups)

semantics.food: cooked chicken breast or rotisserie chicken

ingredients.name: 2/3 cup plain 2% fat Greek yogurt (certified gluten-free if necessary

semantics.food: plain 2% fat Greek yogurt (certified gluten-free if necessary

ingredients.name: 1 pinch salt and pepper, to taste
12 sliced 100% whole grain bread (about 100 calories each)

items.directions: In a large bowl, combine shredded chicken, red onion, apple, grapes, Greek yogurt, lemon juice, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix until well combined.\n\nUsing a 3/4 cup measuring scoop, portion out the chicken salad. Serve with a lettuce leaf and 2 slices of 100% whole grain bread.

items.name: Chicken and Soba Noodle Salad with Ginger Dressing

ingredients.name: 3 cups shiitake mushrooms, stems discarded, caps sliced
2 portions (8 ounces each) boneless, skinless, chicken breasts
4 cups broccoli crowns , cut into 2-inch florets
6 ounces  dry buckwheat soba noodles , (such as Eden Organic)

items.directions:
In a small bowl, combine the soy sauce, vinegar, honey, sesame oil, ginger and garlic. Set aside.

Heat the canola oil in a cast-iron skillet or heavy sauté pan over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and sauté until tender, 4 minutes. Transfer to a large serving bowl. Season the chicken with the salt and pepper before adding it to the skillet, reduce heat to medium, and cook until cooked through, about 5 minutes per side. Place on a cutting board and let rest, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

While the chicken rests, bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil. Add the broccoli and edamame and cook until broccoli is crisp-tender, 4 minutes. With a slotted spoon, transfer the vegetables to the serving bowl with the mushrooms. Add the soba noodles to the boiling water and cook according to package instructions. Drain and rinse with cool water to stop the noodles from overcooking. Add to the noodles to the vegetables in the bowl. Toss with the soy sauce dressing.

Thinly slice the chicken against the grain and place on top of the noodle mixture. Sprinkle green onions over the top and serve. (The salad can be stored in an airtight container for up to 2 days.)

items.name: Zesty Shrimp Lettuce Wrap

ingredients.name: 3/4 pound (340 grams) cooked, peeled and deveined small or medium shrimp

semantics.food: cooked, peeled and deveined small or medium shrimp

ingredients.name: 1 large (70 grams) carrot, peeled and shaved with vegetable peeler or grated

semantics.preparation_notes: peeled and shaved with vegetable peeler or grated

ingredients.name: 1 small (75 grams) yellow bell pepper , finely chopped
1/2 cup (120 grams) no-salt-added canned black beans, rinsed and drained
24 large Boston or butter lettuce leaves, rinsed and patted dry (12 leaves will work if leaves do not need to be stacked)

semantics.preparation_notes: rinsed and patted dry (12 leaves will work if leaves do not need to be stacked)

items.directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce in a medium bowl. (Mixture may be chilled until ready to serve.) Spoon 1/3 cup shrimp salad into each lettuce leaf. Serve immediately.\n\n* If lettuce leaves are small, stack two together before filling.

items.name: Blueberry Muffin Breakfast Mug Cake

ingredients.name: 1/4 cup (60 ml) 2% milk or unsweetened non-dairy
2 teaspoons canola oil or melted coconut oil

semantics.food: canola oil or melted coconut oil

items.directions: In a small bowl, whisk together the flour, oats, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. In a small measuring cup, whisk together the milk, oil and vanilla. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix with a fork until moistened. Stir in the blueberries.\n\nSpoon the batter into a 12–16-ounce (450–473ml) mug. Sprinkle the top with nuts. Microwave on high until the cake has expanded and is firm to the touch, 1 1/2–2 minutes, depending on the wattage of your microwave. Watch closely and do not overcook. Add time in 10-second intervals if the muffin is not done. The muffin will puff up at first, but deflate as it cools.

items.name: Egg Salad Provencal in Lettuce Wraps

ingredients.name: 3 ounce grape tomatoes, about 3/4 cup chopped

items.directions: Peel and chop the eggs and place in a medium bowl. Add the chopped tomatoes, olives, red onion and basil. In a cup, stir the olive oil, vinegar and salt and pour over the egg mixture. Stir to mix.\n\nScoop into lettuce leaves by rounded 1/4-cup servings. Roll to close.

items.name: Baked Veggie Egg Cups

ingredients.name: 1 cup (240 ml) egg whites (or another 6 eggs)

items.directions:
Preheat oven to 375°F (191°C).

Coat 12-cup muffin pan with cooking spray, or line with silicone baking cups. (I coated the silicone baking cups with spray.)

Whisk eggs and egg whites in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a skillet over medium with oil. Add chopped veggies. Cook 5–6 minutes, until they’re a little soft and the onions are fragrant.

Add veggies to eggs. Add in feta and parsley, and mix well.

Use a measuring cup to pour egg mixture evenly into muffin cups, about 1/3 cup each. Bake for 17–20 minutes, or until the egg cups are no longer jiggly and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Allow cups to cool before refrigerating, or enjoy immediately.

items.name: 20-Minute Mango Chicken Bowls
items.directions: In a large skillet, heat oil on medium-high. Season both sides of chicken with salt and pepper. Add chicken to skillet, and cook for 1 to 2 minutes per side, until golden brown.\n\nAdd mangos, bell pepper, broth, green onions, mint, lime juice, lime zest and garlic, and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat to medium. Partially cover, and cook for 5 minutes, until chicken is cooked through. Add rice to skillet, and stir to combine. Cook for 1 minute to heat through. Serve immediately.

items.name: Chicken and Avocado Zucchini-Noodle Bowl

ingredients.name: 1 pound zucchini noodles, from 2 medium zucchinis

items.directions: In a cup, stir the yogurt, olive oil, honey, lemon juice, wasabi and salt. Reserve.\n\nIn each of four wide bowls, spread a cup of spinach, a heaping cup of zucchini noodles and top with 1/4 of the chicken, 4 halved grape tomatoes and 1/4 of the avocado. Drizzle with 2 heaping tablespoons of the yogurt mixture and serve.
